title: Trump's AI action plan: US president signs executive orders; seeks to make America leader in artificial intelligence race
description: Donald Trump signed executive orders to reshape America's AI landscape, targeting 'woke' AI and streamlining data center permits. He aims to make the US an AI export powerhouse, emphasizing the need to win the AI race against other nations. The orders include an action plan to accelerate AI adoption and boost American AI exports, replacing previous Biden-era regulations.

title: Trump vs Columbia: Ivy league school to pay $200 million in landmark settlement; campus protests curbed
description: Columbia University will pay over $220 million and implement policy changes to settle allegations of civil rights violations concerning the protection of Jewish students. The agreement with the Trump administration includes federal oversight, independent monitoring of admissions and hiring, and dismantling discriminatory programs.
author: TOI World Desk
